                <h1>Understanding Black Ice: The Hidden Danger on Roads</h1>
                <p>Black ice texture is a thin layer of transparent ice that forms on road surfaces, appearing nearly indistinguishable from wet pavement. This creates dangerously slippery conditions, often catching drivers off guard. Understanding its properties can help improve safety awareness during cold weather and reduce accident risks.</p>
